title: 0 tiles from `label-maker labels`
body:
Hi - when I run a basic `download` and `labels` I get zero tiles, and I can't tell why. Is there some way that the script could help to diagnose?

FYI, when I run the togo example from the documentation I don't get the 1189 tiles shown in the documentation, I get:

```
 % label-maker labels -c togo-config.json          # exactly the same as the doc example, plus my mapbox API key
Determining labels for each tile
---
Roads: 11 tiles
Buildings: 10 tiles
Total tiles: 12
Writing out labels to data/labels.npz
```

Then when I run my own, which looks like this:

```
{
  "country": "united_kingdom",
  "bounding_box": [51.31258868168418,-0.440826416015625,51.68362528576683,0.23345947265625],
  "zoom": 12,
  "classes": [
    { "name": "Roads", "filter": ["has", "highway"] },
    { "name": "photovoltaic", "filter": ["==", "generator:method", "photovoltaic"] }
  ],
  "imagery": "http://a.tiles.mapbox.com/v4/mapbox.satellite/{z}/{x}/{y}.jpg?access_token=API_KEY",
  "background_ratio": 1,
  "ml_type": "classification"
}
```

I get

```
 % label-maker labels            
Determining labels for each tile
---
Roads: 0 tiles
photovoltaic: 0 tiles
Total tiles: 54
Writing out labels to data/labels.npz
```

Yet the tag I'm querying for is indeed there in the data (see http://overpass-turbo.eu/s/GYQ).

I'd be grateful for any way I can diagnose this and get it up and running.
